race.comment: RITZA JACKSON (2) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when third and beaten 6 lengths at Gosford over 388m in 22.54. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. Expected to feature in the finish again. RED ROCK RAZZLE (3) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from four starts. Scored by 0.8 lengths last time (25.13) in a Grade 5 over 450m at this track. Looks one of the chances. SNOOPY'S ETHICS (1) has been hard to follow lately, running fifth (22.76) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at Richmond Straight. Expected to bounce back to best. WAN CHAI DREAM (7) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish as public elect.
